convinced us to endorse you,

286
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,130
got the bank to approve the loans.

287
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:27,580
Director,

288
00:16:28,670 --> 00:16:30,220
that wasn't hype.

289
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,820
We all discussed and agreed on it,

290
00:16:32,910 --> 00:16:34,420
mutually, right?

291
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:36,060
Well, your brother got tied up
with organized crime.

292
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,100
Now he's gone.

293
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,220
The money's gone too.

294
00:16:39,550 --> 00:16:41,420
He talked a big game
about new energy development,

295
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,490
but nothing ever materialized.

296
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:44,730
I hope

297
00:16:45,670 --> 00:16:47,490
you can face the reality.

298
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:48,730
If this goes on,

299
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:51,010
we'll all be dragged down with you.

300
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,220
The only reality I can face right now is

301
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,530
Wanchuan Mining is the last hope

302
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,820
our family has left.

303
00:16:58,630 --> 00:16:59,340
As long as we still have it,

304
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,890
there's a chance we can recover.

305
00:17:01,030 --> 00:17:01,820
If we sell it,

306
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,650
we're left with nothing.

307
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:05,530
Please help us one more time.

308
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,810
This is me helping you.

309
00:17:12,030 --> 00:17:13,050
Tianlong Company

310
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,620
is one of Dongping's top enterprises,

311
00:17:16,270 --> 00:17:18,050
a major taxpayer
in our development zone.

312
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,220
If they are willing to take over,

313
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,490
it benefits us all.

314
00:17:23,350 --> 00:17:24,620
To put it bluntly,

315
00:17:25,590 --> 00:17:28,810
you're not desperate,
just too blind to see what you've got.

316
00:17:29,480 --> 00:17:30,180
Look,

317
00:17:30,790 --> 00:17:32,180
if you drag it out longer,

318
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,980
the debt ratio with the bank
only gets worse.

319
00:17:35,070 --> 00:17:37,050
Then even if you want to sell,

320
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:38,090
you won't

321
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:40,530
get a good price.

322
00:18:05,030 --> 00:18:06,250
Mr. Li, Director Liu,

323
00:18:06,510 --> 00:18:07,570
welcome. Please, come in.

324
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:11,730
Wow...

325
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:12,980
Director Liu,

326
00:18:13,590 --> 00:18:14,730
isn't this a bit much?

327
00:18:16,310 --> 00:18:17,770
We're celebrating your birthday.

328
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:20,810
I wanted to show you how much I care.

329
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:22,570
- My star prosecutor.
- Watch your steps.

330
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,810
No, it's star prosecutor-general.

331
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:27,180
It's just a birthday.

332
00:18:27,310 --> 00:18:28,460
A dinner at home would've been enough.

333
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,860
There are no outsiders today,

334
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:32,770
just a family gathering.

335
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:34,330
Mr. Li, Director Liu, please.

336
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:38,700
Good evening, Mr. Li, Director Liu.

337
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,420
How come everyone knows me?

338
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,420
You cracked the Wan Hai case.

339
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:46,180
Who in Dongping doesn't know you?

340
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:48,220
Good evening, Mr. Li, Director Liu.

341
00:18:52,030 --> 00:18:53,330
All your dishes are ready, please enjoy.

342
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,050
We're here.

343
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:55,460
Mr. Li is here.

344
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,940
Mr. Li, our birthday star!

345
00:18:58,240 --> 00:18:59,730
Hello, welcome.

346
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:00,380
We've been waiting for you.

347
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,140
See? I really pulled some strings.

348
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:03,620
Come on.

349
00:19:05,510 --> 00:19:06,290
Mr. Xu is here too.

350
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:07,220
We're waiting for you.

351
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:07,980
Chief Judge Wen, come on.

352
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,660
Mr. Li, don't mind us.

353
00:19:09,880 --> 00:19:11,140
We knew today was your birthday.

354
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,460
Didn't even apply through Ms. Lan,

355
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:15,140
we just showed up.

356
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,220
Well, since you're all here,

357
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:17,180
everyone take a seat.

358
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:18,330
Renjun, sit here.

359
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:21,180
Take a seat.

360
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:22,290
Hurry up, sit down.

361
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,380
Director Liu, I have a small request.

362
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:31,330
May I say a few words today?

363
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,140
You absolutely should.

364
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:36,010
All right, with this dinner,

365
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:38,050
I want to make a toast.

366
00:19:39,310 --> 00:19:41,140
Originally, Liu Yun and I planned to

367
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,220
have a quiet birthday dinner
for Renjun at home.

368
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:44,420
But

369
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:46,900
he just wrapped up a major case,

370
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:47,940
we thought he could relax a bit.

371
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:49,980
Didn't expect so many of you

372
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,530
would show up
for our little family dinner.

373
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,330
Let me guess,

374
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:57,010
this was your idea, right, Liu Yun?

375
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,940
I might have encouraged it a little too.

376
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,010
Since you're here,

377
00:20:04,240 --> 00:20:05,730
I can only welcome you.

378
00:20:06,110 --> 00:20:07,290
Of course, we'll feed you.

379
00:20:09,110 --> 00:20:11,250
You've all worked hard lately.

380
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:13,730
It's only right we have dinner together.

381
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,050
Just don't forget the rules.

382
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,770
Even though the big case is over,

383
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:21,330
but

384
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:23,010
we still need to stay humble
and disciplined.

385
00:20:25,070 --> 00:20:26,180
Come on, everyone.

386
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,570
Ms. Lan is right.

387
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:30,660
Right!

388
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:31,530
Come on.

389
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:32,810
Can you be serious?

390
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:33,460
Okay.

391
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:34,570
I'm being very sincere.

392
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:34,980
Come on.

393
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,940
Thank you.

394
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:36,730
Renjun.

395
00:20:42,070 --> 00:20:42,700
Take your seats.

396
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:43,940
Well, I've got to

397
00:20:44,070 --> 00:20:46,180
fill this one for Ms. Lan.

398
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,700
You wanna make a toast?

399
00:20:48,270 --> 00:20:49,570
Comes straight from the heart.

400
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,250
Ms. Lan.

401
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:53,770
Without your support,

402
00:20:54,590 --> 00:20:56,460
we wouldn't be where we are today.

403
00:20:57,350 --> 00:20:58,140
You set the big picture,

404
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,940
your direction

405
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,490
is the path we follow.

406
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:04,090
Twenty years ago,
you were the one who guided me.

407
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,770
Today, you still are.

408
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:07,860
This one's for you.

409
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:08,420
Thank you.

410
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:12,660
I'd also like to toast Ms. Lan.

411
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:14,730
Ms. Lan...

412
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,090
You sit down.

413
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:17,180
Alright, I'll sit.

414
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:18,940
Ms. Lan,

415
00:21:19,510 --> 00:21:20,380
to be honest,

416
00:21:21,110 --> 00:21:22,730
in the middle of
handling this Wan Hai case,

417
00:21:23,310 --> 00:21:25,010
I had my doubts.

418
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:28,180
But seeing you and Mr. Li
being so determined,

419
00:21:28,510 --> 00:21:30,700
leading us forward despite the pressure,

420
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:32,090
that cleared my doubts.

421
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:33,010
I will

422
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:35,490
learn more from you and Mr. Li
in the future.

423
00:21:35,880 --> 00:21:36,420
Here's to that.

424
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:37,330
Thank you.

425
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:42,730
Well,

426
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:43,900
Ms. Lan,

427
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,090
I, I have to toast you too.

428
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:47,490
Just say it from your seat.

429
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:48,940
Sit down.

430
00:21:49,550 --> 00:21:50,010
Okay.

431
00:21:51,510 --> 00:21:52,090
Ms. Lan,

432
00:21:52,680 --> 00:21:55,220
first, thank you for your understanding.

433
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:56,380
everyone knows,

434
00:21:57,030 --> 00:21:58,010
my body

435
00:21:59,030 --> 00:21:59,810
keeps letting me down.

436
00:22:00,510 --> 00:22:01,380
I'm anxious about it too.

437
00:22:01,790 --> 00:22:03,140
I'll do my best

438
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:05,140
to recover quickly,

439
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:07,090
so I can contribute more

440
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:08,490
like Mr. Li

441
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:10,290
and Chief Judge Wen.

442
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:11,660
Ms. Lan,

443
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:12,860
here's to you.

444
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:22,010
I...

445
00:22:22,590 --> 00:22:23,050
would like to...

446
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:24,530
apologize first.

447
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:26,700
Well,

448
00:22:27,550 --> 00:22:28,140
I know

449
00:22:29,030 --> 00:22:30,700
the fact that I'm still
sitting here today

450
00:22:31,550 --> 00:22:32,570
is because of Ms. Lan's

451
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,010
trust in me.

452
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:36,180
Actually,

453
00:22:37,590 --> 00:22:38,530
I didn't handle this well.

454
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:40,810
Since I took on this case,

455
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:42,900
I was eager

456
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:44,330
to get it indicted.

457
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,290
I believed Zhang Wenjing had issues,

458
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:49,810
so I asked Mr. Sun to look into her.

459
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:51,940
Turns out she really did.

460
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:55,460
But in the end,
we still didn't handle it well.

461
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:59,140
So however I'm dealt with,
I accept it.

462
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,700
Today, I want to

463
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:03,140
apologize to you,

464
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:04,980
Ms. Lan.

465
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:06,620
I've always

466
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,330
worked diligently all these years.

467
00:23:09,310 --> 00:23:10,770
If there was a flaw in this case,

468
00:23:10,790 --> 00:23:11,290
that flaw

469
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:13,180
was me.

470
00:23:14,070 --> 00:23:15,900
I let you down.

471
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,180
I failed to live up to your trust.

472
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:19,490
I am sorry.

473
00:23:23,310 --> 00:23:24,770
And, Mr. Li,

474
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,730
this one's for you.

475
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:29,900
My reach is limited.

476
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:32,530
From now on,

477
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:34,180
I'll prove myself with actions.

478
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:35,220
Cheers.

479
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:54,770
Alright, Xie. You were
thinking about the bigger picture.

480
00:23:55,270 --> 00:23:57,460
I believe Ms. Lan and everyone here

481
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:58,250
can understand.

482
00:23:58,920 --> 00:23:59,620
Right, Mr. Li?

483
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:07,010
No case goes perfectly.

484
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:08,330
Besides,

485
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:10,900
Hongfei,

486
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:13,090
your intention was good.

487
00:24:13,590 --> 00:24:14,330
Nothing wrong with that.

488
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:18,620
This case was incredibly complicated,

489
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,570
had all kinds of mixed-up clues.

490
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:24,730
It's understandable to make mistakes.

491
00:24:29,310 --> 00:24:30,900
But in the future,

492
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:33,490
we need to be even more careful,

493
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,700
avoid repeating the same errors.

494
00:24:37,310 --> 00:24:39,050
Let's turn the page on this.

495
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,460
We won't mention it again.

496
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:43,050
Thank you.

497
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:48,380
Mr. Li.

498
00:25:01,510 --> 00:25:02,140
Director Liu.

499
00:25:08,310 --> 00:25:08,900
Sit down.

500
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:09,330
Xie,

501
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:11,940
we all get where you're coming from.

502
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:14,570
Don't be too upset.

503
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:16,730
It's okay.

504
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:44,730
How was it?

505
00:25:46,550 --> 00:25:47,810
I went to five law firms.

506
00:25:50,350 --> 00:25:51,220
All rejected me.

507
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:58,090
Don't panic.

508
00:26:01,030 --> 00:26:01,900
We'll think of something else.

509
00:26:03,510 --> 00:26:04,770
And if not,

510
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:06,660
you could try something different.

511
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,220
Try something different?

512
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,620
Like what?

513
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:16,050
Civil service?

514
00:26:17,270 --> 00:26:18,460
Prosecutor? Judge?

515
00:26:19,830 --> 00:26:21,010
Would they even take me?

516
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,570
I'm a criminal defense lawyer.

517
00:26:26,790 --> 00:26:28,490
Graduated from a top law school.

518
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,620
Why would they want me?

519
00:26:32,310 --> 00:26:34,010
When they need me to be a 'criminal',

520
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,010
they could just label me as one

521
00:26:36,030 --> 00:26:36,860
and lock me up.

522
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,810
When they need me to be clean,

523
00:26:38,830 --> 00:26:39,700
I'm declared innocent

524
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,530
and released.

525
00:26:41,070 --> 00:26:42,660
Can the law be used like that?

526
00:26:45,400 --> 00:26:47,940
You're venting now,

527
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,050
it's pointless.

528
00:26:50,550 --> 00:26:52,460
Who told you to take this case?

529
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:53,530
What if you didn't take it?

530
00:26:54,830 --> 00:26:57,730
You got out safely now,

531
00:26:58,510 --> 00:26:59,420
live with that.

532
00:26:59,960 --> 00:27:01,530
How could I not take it?

533
00:27:03,790 --> 00:27:05,770
They were twisting the facts,
don't you know that?

534
00:27:06,830 --> 00:27:08,660
I'm the legal adviser to Wan Group.

535
00:27:08,830 --> 00:27:10,180
I couldn't just walk away.

536
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:12,530
What did you say

537
00:27:12,550 --> 00:27:13,490
when I was arrested?

538
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:16,140
Zhang Wenjing,

539
00:27:17,030 --> 00:27:17,700
you are suspected of participating

540
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,140
in the Wan Hai organized crime case.

541
00:27:20,070 --> 00:27:21,460
[Arrest Warrant]
You are now under arrest.

542
00:27:22,070 --> 00:27:22,460
Cuff her.

543
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:25,250
What are you doing?

544
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:26,180
All right.

545
00:27:26,310 --> 00:27:27,290
Go back to your work.

546
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:28,380
Let's not escalate this.

547
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:29,250
Go.

548
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:30,860
Zhang Wenjing,

549
00:27:31,880 --> 00:27:32,660
go with the police for now.

550
00:27:33,590 --> 00:27:34,140
I've got you.

551
00:27:35,790 --> 00:27:37,180
You looked me in the eye and told me

552
00:27:37,350 --> 00:27:38,940
to believe you, that you've got me.

553
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:39,980
And then?

554
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:41,730
You were the first to walk away.

555
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,140
You left me alone.

556
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,620
No one answered,
no matter how hard I cried for help.

557
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:45,700
What do you expect me to do?

558
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:47,290
What can I possibly do by myself?

559
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:48,330
Tell me!

560
00:27:49,350 --> 00:27:50,490
What can I do?

561
00:27:52,110 --> 00:27:53,180
When I graduated from college,

562
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:54,090
remember what you said back then?

563
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:54,940
You said,

564
00:27:55,270 --> 00:27:57,570
'Justice has no right to be late.'

565
00:27:58,070 --> 00:27:58,490
Right?

566
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:01,180
'Justice that comes too late
isn't justice.'

567
00:28:01,200 --> 00:28:02,620
'It is at best a truth.'

568
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:03,770
Weren't those your words?

569
00:28:05,510 --> 00:28:07,180
And now you're telling me this?

570
00:28:16,110 --> 00:28:16,620
Forget it.

571
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:18,980
Some things,

572
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,220
you don't need to know.

573
00:28:21,310 --> 00:28:22,490
